During a speech at Virginia Theological Seminary in Alexandria, Virginia, President Biden expressed optimism that the worst of the COVID-19 pandemic would soon be behind us. He stated that if everyone continues on the current path, the situation will improve. The President also mentioned that a significant portion of the American public will be vaccinated by the end of the summer. He plans to make an announcement regarding the progress of vaccinations at the White House, stating that over 200 million shots will have been administered within the next 25 days. He reassured the public that the vaccines are effective against the various strains of the virus. However, he emphasized the importance of continuing to wear masks, practice proper hand hygiene, and maintain social distancing. The President also joked about not following his own advice on social distancing.